Brik, you need to stop sniffing glue bubba.  This is a Warrior board, ergo we will talk about things from a, you guessed it, Warrior perspective.  We don't require the Shadow Knights over on the Shadow Knight board 'open their eyes to actual class balance'.   Hell for AGES they have dominated in the taunt arena, and we didn't raise much of a fuss about it because we dominated in the tank arena.<br>
<br>
Well guess what, we don't dominate in the tank arena anymore, at least not by more than a hair.  So yeah, we're pissed as hell about that because they have given our functionality to the Knights and the Monks and given us SQUAT in return.<br>
<br>
You want to talk class balance?  Great, we can talk class balance.  But when other classes come to OUR board and tell us we have tunnel vision when we are annoyed about getting the shaft for the last two expansions, that annoys me.<br>
<br>
Do Shadow Knights have issues?  You bet.  Do Paladins have issues?  You bet.  Are they discussed on forums for those classes?  You bet.  So how about you give us the respect of letting us discuss our issues on our board without being a pill about it? <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukrazrussian.showPublicProfile?language=EN>KrazRussian</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 11<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/30/02 8:18:46 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2132.topic&index=90>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: class definitions</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;what ability defines Shadow Knights in the <br>
