<br>
Anywhere between 1st and 3rd best melee solo class. Best Rampage tank in the game. Situationally better pullers than monks. Harmtouch. Do you want to know WHY you are not defined as a class by a certain ability; becuase you are a HYBRID. I think this needs to be pounded into the heads of about 80% of the hybrids that post here praising /disc defensive and saying warriors are overpowered or balanced.<br>
<br>
a HYBRID means you are a combination of two parent classes and have the abilities of both, while mastering none. Seriously, don't @#%$ bow to /disc when you know dick about how good it is, k? I hate using that disc. I hate being a 3-minute wonder. I use it, exclusively on raids, only when I have to. It is NOT a class defining ability, nor should it be. Having better mitigation is something warriors should ALREADY HAVE, not use a 3-minute prosthetic with 12 minute refresh that makes our DPS even more pathetic than it is now. <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> &quot;the truth is, Shadowknights have NO functioning defining role either. Im sure mages and necros, and paladins could add their name to the same list. Of course those classes actually have NOTHING that defines them....&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Mage: modRod-2. This is arguably just as powerful as Complete Heal on the mobs that need it (which is quite a few; especially in SoL where mobs take more than 3 min to kill). <br>
<br>
Necro: Twitch, DPS, Group healing (via Theft of Vitae).<br>
<br>
Paladin: Group heal (you can't @#%$ with the usefullness of WAve of Prexuss till you fight in SoL and see that a class that does just about as much damage as you (warriors) do, has maybe 700less HP, but can chain cast group 660-heal about 6-7 times during a fight). Rampage tank, backup healer, emergency healer (Only instant Cheal with new AA's). Bmb good too.<br>
<br>
Shadowknight: Rampage tank (best in game probably; better than monks; lot better than warriors if you know how rampage works). Their new agro spell is huge to a raids success; it really helps warriors keep agro. Group atk buffs, DPS.<br>
<br>
Keep in mind, the warrior &quot;class-defining&quot; ability is pretty much raid-only. In fact, it's a tanking-only ability. THat, keep in mind, is their one class-defining ability. <p><center><p><font size = 3 colo = "blue"><b>Wilhelmm D'Averam<br>Warlord of the Apocalypse</b></font></p></center>

